The Last Hero

by Wayde Bairstow

In a land far, far away. There lay the kingdom of June. A peaceful nation with a population of 6 million and home to the realms mightiest heroes; The Band of Heroes the battle-hardened warrior “Maximus”, the mystic Wizard “Elder Frank” and the deceptive Rogue “Tulip”. In the kingdom of June the band of heroes are revered by all.

They are the staunch protectors of the kingdom, protecting those from any threat that any normal person can’t face. Whether it, be a colossus troll that is terrorising the local towns or a curse that is turning everyone into cheese wheels. Almost everyone is inspired by the band of heroes within the kingdom of June. Well almost everyone.

Within the band of heroes, there is a fourth member that lacks the capability to be a hero. This fourth member just so happened to be the protagonist of the story *sigh*. His name is Dave.

Dave is your typical, run of the mill squire of the group. Managing the group’s gear, cleaning their armour, cooking the groups meals, organizing the groups spoils, pretty much Dave’s daily routine in a nutshell. Though Dave is contempt going about a boring life, he still dreams of becoming a hero along the group so that he can join in the privileges of being one of them. Though he may not know it now, he will soon learn that dream of his may come true, as the kingdom of June has recently been put in a troublesome spot.

A while ago, the castle fortress “Duran” that overlooks the kingdom June on top the mountain “Jural” was attacked by “Magnus the Great Dragon” a prominent and feared enemy of the kingdom. After wiping out the defenders of the castle, Magnus claimed the mountain Jural as its new home. Without any one defending the castle, it was later claimed by a group of marauders that worshiped the dragon, revering it as their god and as well using the castle as a means to raid helpless villages for spoils to give to the dragon. With the threat of a Dragon nesting near the kingdom and the constant assaults from the marauders, the King sent a request to the band of heroes to go and slay the Dragon threat.

Accepting the call, the heroes within descended upon the dragon’s lair in hopes of claiming the bounty and the glory of killing a Great Dragon. As quickly as they went, they never came back. The band of heroes were brutally slaughtered by the Dragon and part of their remains sent back to the King as a message. With the band of heroes dead there was no one left to defeat the dragon. The King was left with no choice but to extend the bounty of killing the dragon to anyone. One after another other heroes tried their hand at killing the dragon only to be swiftly defeated by the obstacles of the mountain. With the Kings plan failing, the kingdom fell into a state of fear. But unbeknownst to them there was still one hero left that had a chance at defeating the Dragon.

The unofficial fourth member of the band of heroes that was left behind to do the groups errands. Dave.

Your Bedroom
This is your living quarters. Its currently in a unkept state with trash and clothing strewn across the room. Due to your busy work with the Band of Heroes you never had any time to clean or organize your room.
You can see a Bed, a Window, a Pile of trash and a Wardrobe.
You can go south.
> open window

> open window

You pry the window open, allowing clean air to breeze through into the room. As you hold your face into the wind you hear a loud buzzing noise fly past your face. You realize that a bee has flown into your room.
> squash bee

> squash bee

You squash the bee with both your hands. It lets out a loud "POP" sound as it gets squashed between your hands. It then falls down to the ground with a slow buzz.
