> use street shark extract on gregory

> use street shark extract on gregory

You stab the syringe into Gregory's chest, injecting him with Street shark extract. Gregory springs back to life, jumping in the air and then landing back on the ground with a thud. Even though he had been injected with a expermental drug, he seems fine.
> speak to gregory

> speak to gregory

"Well that was some powerful stuff. I can feel this old heart of mine beating again. Now...what was I doing. From what I last remeber I was running to your house to tell you something, but my heart gave out when I got to your door. What was I going to tell you?"

"OH JURAGS BALLS, I REMEBER NOW! Listen Dave,  the kingdom needs your help. The Band of Heroes were defeated by the Great Dragon Magnus ontop of mount Jural and there's no one left except you to defeat the dragon."

Dumbfounded and confused not only by the fact that The Band of Heroes that you had worked for were defeated but also that Gregory said that you can defeat the dragon. You ask Gregory why he thinks that you can defeat the dragon in which he replies.

"Well, you've served The Band of Heroes over the years, so by proxy must have picked some knowledge on how to defeat the dragon. Also you’re the only person left alive to deal with this, the rest of the other adventurers died off or ran away in fear."

Unsatisfied by his answer, you at first refused his request.

"Look, I know this is a really odd and slightly insane request, but I’ll give you some time to think on it. Once you've come to a decision, come meet me at the Royal Castle and I’ll explain further."

And with that, Gregory disappears in a cloud of cheap magical smoke.

You ponder on his request for a while, sitting on the nearby chair in a thoughtful position. After several minutes you reluctantly decide to take Gregory up on his request. (Plus the authour was too lazy to do the Refusal of the Call part of this story).

But before you set forth on your journey, you must first gear yourself up with armour and a weapon. This can be done within Workshop.
